value.title: Biden seeks five-year extension of New START arms treaty with Russia: source
value.excerpt: U.S. President Joe Biden will seek a five-year extension to the New START arms control treaty with Russia, a source familiar with the matter said on Thursday.

value.title: New York Times contributor apologizes for tweet suggesting Biden should 'lynch Mike Pence'
value.excerpt: A contributing opinion writer for The New York Times is under fire for a tweet that jokingly suggested former Vice President Mike Pence be lynched in order to unify the country.

value.title: Biden has ‘bigger issues’ to worry about than following own mask mandate: Psaki
value.excerpt: President Biden has “bigger issues” to worry about than wearing a face mask at the Lincoln Memorial as he celebrated his Inauguration, according to White House press secretary Jennifer Psaki.

value.title: Biden order seeks stronger workplace safety rules, signaling a more worker friendly approach
value.excerpt: The Executive Order could lead to an emergency standard for businesses — a set of a regulations they would have to comply with, like mask-wearing, that advocates say is necessary to combat the pandemic.

value.title: Biden demands decency, promising staff members 'I will fire you on the spot' if they disrespect others
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden conducted a swearing-in ceremony by video conference Wednesday with hundreds of new government staff members.

value.title: McConnell: Biden ‘took several big steps in the wrong direction’ on Day One
value.excerpt: Just one day after President Biden spoke of unity in his inaugural address to the nation, Senate Minority Leader Mitch McConnell says the Democrat president has headed in "the wrong direction."

value.title: Ivanka Trump and Jared Kushner move out of DC and lease luxury condo in Miami
value.excerpt: Ivanka Trump and Jared Kushner have moved out of their Washington, DC, home, and have signed a one-year lease on a luxury condo in Miami at the Arte, an expensive oceanfront residential building, a source familiar with the couple's move confirmed to CNN.

value.title: President Biden signs order mandating masks on planes: Will it reduce number of in-flight scofflaws?
value.excerpt: Airlines require masks and ban passengers who won't comply. A new federal mask rule signed by Biden Thursday gives them muscle to enforce it.

value.title: Tara Reade says watching Biden's inauguration was 'exceptionally hard': I want to 'wake up from a nightmare'
value.excerpt: Tara Reade, the former Senate staffer who came forward during the 2020 campaign  with a sexual assault allegation against Joe Biden, is speaking out about her former boss taking the oath of office as the 46th president of the United States.

value.title: House expected to approve waiver for Biden's Defense Secretary nominee Lloyd Austin
value.excerpt: President Biden's nominee for Secretary of Defense is expected to clear an important hurdle Thursday in his pathway to confirmation of the new cabinet.

value.title: Logan: Media institutions won't 'admit they were wrong about so many stories' during Trump era
value.excerpt: Affiliates of the mainstream media will not admit they were wrong about how they conducted journalism during the Trump administration, Fox Nation host Lara Logan said on Thursday.

value.title: Durbin says Trump impeachment trial 'unresolved,' but calls it a 'priority'
value.excerpt: Senate Majority Whip Dick Durbin on Thursday said he expects the House may send the article of impeachment to the Senate in "a day or two," maintaining that a trial for former President Donald Trump is "a priority."

value.title: Charlottesville Inspired Biden to Run. Now It Has a Message for Him.
value.excerpt: The white supremacist rally in 2017 prefigured the rise of right-wing violence in President Trump’s name. Now, as President Biden calls for national unity, residents say it requires accountability first.

value.title: LIVE UPDATES: Anti-Biden Antifa protesters take to the streets in Portland, Seattle overnight
value.excerpt: At least eight adults were arrested for crimes ranging from rioting and possession of a destructive device to reckless burning.

value.title: Pence touts time as VP, including Hoosier Justice Barrett, in return to Indiana: 'There's no place like home'
value.excerpt: Former Vice President Pence wished new President Biden and Vice President Harris well as he returned to Indiana on Wednesday afternoon, while also expressing gratitude for his time as vice president.

value.title: ‘Celebrating America’ review: Earnest inauguration special encapsulates President Joe Biden
value.excerpt: Celebrating America” traded the usual inauguration night balls for socially distanced performances from around the country, spotlights of “everyday heroes,” and solemn acknowledgments of the extraordinarily tough few years the country has muscled through to get to this moment.

value.title: Theologian Russell Moore Has a Message for Christians Who Still Worship Donald Trump
value.excerpt: If you can defend this, you can defend anything,” wrote Russell Moore, a theologian who is also the president of the Ethics and Religious Liberty Commission (ERLC) of the Southern Baptist Convention (SBC),

value.title: First 100 days of Biden, Obama, Clinton: Escalating spending to address economic challenge
value.excerpt: The first 100 days of a two-term presidency mark about 3% of the eight-year span, but since President Franklin Delano Roosevelt, this brief early window of opportunity has been used to judge a new commander in chief’s agenda.

value.title: In the end, Mike Pence showed both his guts, and class
value.excerpt: The appalling Jan. 6 insurrection at the Capitol also targeted then-Vice President Mike Pence’s life, yet he still rose to the occasion to fulfill his duty with great courage, and he demonstrated class in attending Wednesday’s inauguration of Joe Biden.

value.title: Morgan Lewis, Trump's longtime tax counsel, prepares for split
value.excerpt: Morgan, Lewis & Bockius said Wednesday it was stepping away from advising Donald Trump on tax matters, leaving the former president and his businesses further isolated from the country's largest law firms.

value.title: Fox News host Judge Jeanine lobbied Trump during his last few hours in office to pardon her ex-husband. It worked.
value.excerpt: Fox News host Judge Jeanine successfully lobbied former President Donald Trump in an eleventh-hour effort to pardon her ex-husband in the final hours of Trump's presidency, CNN has learned.

value.title: Biden ditches military flags as part of Oval Office makeover
value.excerpt: With new presidents come new White House decorations – especially in the commander-in-chief’s official workplace, the Oval Office.

value.title: Biden to new administration staffers: Be nice to others or 'I will fire you on the spot'
value.excerpt: President Biden warned new members of his administration Wednesday that he’ll fire them “on the spot” if they fail to treat others nicely.

value.title: Biden coronavirus adviser hawked masks he said would 'deactivate' COVID-19
value.excerpt: Andy Slavitt, an incoming White House adviser for the coronavirus response team, cut ties with a mask manufacturing company that had offered him paid promotions.

value.title: GOP looks to Biden administration to ‘lower the temperature’ but voice skepticism
value.excerpt: President Biden made a direct appeal to pro-Trump supporters and Republicans across the nation who did not vote for him to become the 46th president of the United States, calling for everyone to "stop the shouting and lower the temperature."
